  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 230°C/ 210°C (fan)/ gas 8 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Cut your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into thick wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>sweet potato wedges</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), skin-side down, drizzle with<strong> vegetable oil, </strong>and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 30 min or until crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/480.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/480.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/480.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/480.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/480.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the wedges are cooking, peel and finely chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong>,<strong> garlic</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, and cook for 3 min or until the onion has softened, then add your <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p>",
      "order": 2,
